      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STAR SIRIUS (4) continues to leave herself plenty to do when straightening, but finally had enough in reserve last start to reel them all in. If they roll along again, she'll be cutting them down late. CASH (5) has rediscovered his best since returning from his unsuccessful QLD sojourn. He backs up quickly and gets his first look at the mile. Expect him to be right there when they quicken. FAST BUBBLES (2) couldn't quite match STAR SIRIUS last time, but he's at peak fitness now and draws well for gun hoop Jake Toeroek, who sticks. A SAMURAI MIND (1) comes through stronger races and gets weight relief with the 3kg claim. He loves the mile and should be right in the thick of it. BROWN NOSE DAY GAL (6) is a mare in form and simply going too well to ignore. Worth including at the minimum.",
